steps.instruction:
- But the breasts in half
- Cut the onion very thin
- Season both sides of the breast half with garlic salt and pepper
- Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat
- Cook the breasts until brown (3 to 4 minutes per side)
- Add onions, cook and cook and stir until the onion browns (3 to 4 minutes)
- Pour diced tomatoes and balsamic vinegar over chicken
- Season with basil, oregano, rosemary and thyme
- Simmer till the chicken is no longer pink in the middle (about 15 minutes)
- Make sure it is done by putting a thermometer into the thickest breast and keep cooking till it reads at least 165F
